```class Solution {
public:
    int minFlipsMonoIncr(string s) {
        int flips = 0, ones = 0;
        for (char c : s) {
            ones += c == '1';
            flips = min(flips + (c == '0'), ones);
        }
        return flips;
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We iterate through the string once, keeping track of the number of ones seen so far. For each zero, we update the minimum number of flips by taking the minimum of the current number of flips plus one (for flipping this zero) and the number of ones seen so far (for flipping all previous ones).

